Full Description: INDIGENOUS CHOCOLATE is a Collective Common-Law Trademark and Term that defines CHOCOLATE that is made and produced by the same Indigenous Peoples at the only legal and scientifically referenced ORIGIN and SOURCE of Theobroma cacao.
